content:
Pause Call Recording to Honor Customer Privacy

Some companies automatically record calls for training and quality purposes. Your customers and your company sometimes prefer not to record certain information for privacy and legal compliance reasons.

Honor your customer’s privacy and protect your company by pausing the recording when sensitive information is exchanged. Resume the recording when it’s appropriate.

To pause and resume call recordings, you need Control Call Recordings permission.

Call recording is turned on by default with Amazon Connect. An administrator can configure when calls are recorded in contact flows.

All users must agree to being recorded for data protection reasons. To pause the recording, click Recording in the Omni-Channel utility or the Phone component. To resume recording, click the button again.
title: Pause Call Recording for Customer Privacy
